{"id":4859,"date":"2026-02-04T09:32:35","date_gmt":"2026-02-04T04:02:35","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/?page_id=4859"},"modified":"2026-02-04T09:40:53","modified_gmt":"2026-02-04T04:10:53","slug":"brhad-bhagavatamrta-3","status":"publish","type":"page","link":"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/brhad\/japan\/part-3\/","title":{"rendered":"Brhad Bhagavatamrta &#8211; 3"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-block-embed-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\n<iframe title=\"Evening class by Bhanu Swami (6th Dec 2017)\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" src=\"https:\/\/www.youtube.com\/embed\/xgtU4r1Jx5s?feature=oembed\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share\" referrerpolicy=\"strict-origin-when-cross-origin\" allowfullscreen><\/iframe>\n<\/div><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\"><strong>Brhad Bhagavatamrta -3| HH Bhanu swami Maharaj | ISKCON Japan | 6th Dec 2017<\/strong><br><br>jaya r\u0101dh\u0101-m\u0101dhava ku\u00f1ja-vih\u0101r\u012b<br>gop\u012bjana-vallabha giri-vara-dh\u0101r\u012b<br>ya\u015bod\u0101-nandana vraja-jana-ra\u00f1jana<br>yamun\u0101-t\u012bra-vana-c\u0101r\u012b<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\">Hare K\u1e5b\u1e63\u1e47a Hare K\u1e5b\u1e63\u1e47a K\u1e5b\u1e63\u1e47a K\u1e5b\u1e63\u1e47a Hare Hare<br>Hare R\u0101ma Hare R\u0101ma R\u0101ma R\u0101ma Hare Hare<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\">Jaya Prabhup\u0101da Jaya Prabhup\u0101da &nbsp;<br>Prabhup\u0101da Jaya Prabhup\u0101da<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\">nama o\u1e41 vi\u1e63\u1e47u-p\u0101d\u0101ya k\u1e5b\u1e63\u1e47a-pre\u1e63\u1e6dh\u0101ya bh\u016b-tale<br>\u015br\u012bmate bhaktived\u0101nta-sv\u0101min iti n\u0101mine<br>namas te s\u0101rasvate deve gaura-v\u0101\u1e47\u012b-prac\u0101ri\u1e47e<br>nirvi\u015be\u1e63a-\u015b\u016bnyav\u0101di-p\u0101\u015bc\u0101tya-de\u015ba-t\u0101ri\u1e47e<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\">jaya \u015br\u012b-k\u1e5b\u1e63\u1e47a-caitanya prabhu-nity\u0101nanda<br>\u015br\u012b-advaita gad\u0101dhara \u015br\u012bv\u0101s\u0101di-gaura-bhakta-v\u1e5bnda<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\"><\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignfull size-full\"><img fetchpriority=\"high\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"903\" height=\"508\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-59.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4860\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-59.png 903w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-59-300x169.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-59-768x432.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 903px) 100vw, 903px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\">Hare K\u1e5b\u1e63\u1e47a Hare K\u1e5b\u1e63\u1e47a K\u1e5b\u1e63\u1e47a K\u1e5b\u1e63\u1e47a Hare Hare<br>Hare R\u0101ma Hare R\u0101ma R\u0101ma R\u0101ma Hare Hare<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>HH Bhanu Swami Maharaj:<\/strong>&nbsp;Hare Krishna. [Conversation aside]. So, this whole story is a conversation between Jaimini and Janmejaya, and within that we have,&nbsp;Pariksit speaking to his mother.&nbsp;So, first of all, Uttara asked Parikshit what&#8217;s the essence of everything? And then Pariksit replied by telling the story of Narada Muni and how Narada Muni searched out everywhere for who is the highest recipient of mercy [Laughs]. So, it was concluded that the Gopis of Vrindavan were the greatest recipients of Krishna&#8217;s mercy.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignfull size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"903\" height=\"508\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-60.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4861\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-60.png 903w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-60-300x169.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-60-768x432.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 903px) 100vw, 903px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>So, now another story begins. This is the second part of Brhad Bhagavatamrta.&nbsp;The first one was called Finding Out the Essence, and this one is called Glories of Goloka. So, now Uttara begins to ask Pariksit another question, but first she gives a long explanation [Laughs] that lead up to her question. So, she starts by describing regular dharma, where householders do pious acts and nitya, naimittika&nbsp;and kamya karmas, and then they get results of going to Bhuvar and Svargaloka, etc, for enjoyment.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>Nitya Karma&nbsp;:<\/strong>&nbsp;So, as part of the varnashram system, there are what are called nitya karmas, or activities that one must do every day. Nitya means daily. So, these daily activities are obligatory actions that you do daily.&nbsp;I think bathing&nbsp;using mantras, doing sandhya vandana,&nbsp;that is, you recite your Gayatri mantra with introductory prayers and then closing prayers, fire sacrifices, etc. These are daily activities that a brahmana especially should do.<br><\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Naimittika Karma&nbsp;:<\/strong>&nbsp;And naimittika karmas refers to periodic activities.&nbsp;They&#8217;re not done everyday, but sometimes may&nbsp;be a few months&nbsp;once, you do one of these activities, such as shraddha rites and samskaras.&nbsp;<br><\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Kamya Karma<\/strong>&nbsp;: And then we have kamya karmas, which means we do certain activities to fulfill specific desires.&nbsp;For instance, if you want to have children, then you do some specific sacrifices and vratas, etc,&nbsp;for that. So, the normal householder follows dharma with desire to get some elevation and go to Svargaloka.<\/li>\n<\/ol>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignfull size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"903\" height=\"508\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-61.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4862\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-61.png 903w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-61-300x169.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-61-768x432.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 903px) 100vw, 903px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>If the householder becomes very detached and does not want those results, but he simply does activities as part of duty as svadharma, then he goes beyond Svargaloka.&nbsp;He can go to Maharloka and Janaloka. And if they purify themselves further, then they can get liberation. So, those with desires take birth again and again.&nbsp;Those that start niskama and stop the desires, then eventually they get liberated.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignfull size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"903\" height=\"508\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-110.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4911\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-110.png 903w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-110-300x169.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-110-768x432.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 903px) 100vw, 903px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>So, those with desires may go to Svargaloka, and then if you start getting more purified, you go to Maharloka, Janaloka, Tapaloka, Satyaloka, and if you are completely pure, then you can get moksha, liberation.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignfull size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"903\" height=\"508\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-62.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4863\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-62.png 903w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-62-300x169.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-62-768x432.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 903px) 100vw, 903px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>And if one is brahmachari, vanaprastha&nbsp;and sannyasi, then because they are all detached, they don&#8217;t have any desires for Svargaloka&nbsp;etc, they can go to Maharloka, Janaloka, Tapaloka, Satyaloka.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignfull size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"903\" height=\"508\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-63.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4864\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-63.png 903w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-63-300x169.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-63-768x432.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 903px) 100vw, 903px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p><br>So, you can actually get liberation in two ways. You can go a gradual process or a quick process. So, the gradual process is used by many yogis, and they go through upper planetary systems gradually, they get a little enjoyment in these places, etc, and finally they get liberation.&nbsp;Other persons who are completely renounced, and completely dedicated to spiritual life, can get quicker liberation.<br><\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignfull size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"903\" height=\"508\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-64.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4865\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-64.png 903w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-64-300x169.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-64-768x432.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 903px) 100vw, 903px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Similarly, devotees may have desires also, material desires, so they can also gradually elevate [Laughs] in different planetary systems, and then go to the Lord&#8217;s abode&nbsp;in&nbsp;Vaikuntha. If they practice pure bhakti, then they can go very, very quickly.&nbsp;<br><\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignfull size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"903\" height=\"508\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-65.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4866\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-65.png 903w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-65-300x169.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-65-768x432.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 903px) 100vw, 903px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>So, even liberated souls have difficulty going to\u00a0Vaikuntha,\u00a0but devotees get there very easily.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignfull size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"903\" height=\"508\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-66.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4867\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-66.png 903w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-66-300x169.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-66-768x432.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 903px) 100vw, 903px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>So, Uttara begins to describe different types of devotees. There are some devotees who are attached to knowledge, so a little bit of jnana is mixed with their bhakti.\u00a0<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignfull size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"903\" height=\"508\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-67.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4868\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-67.png 903w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-67-300x169.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-67-768x432.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 903px) 100vw, 903px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>So, he gives an example like Bharat, on austerities, etc. So, they don&#8217;t desire just mukti and merging in Brahman, they want the Lord, but there&#8217;s a little bit of jnana mixed in their bhakti.<br><\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignfull size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"903\" height=\"508\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-68.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4869\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-68.png 903w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-68-300x169.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-68-768x432.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 903px) 100vw, 903px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Then we have persons who do unmixed bhakti, pure suddha bhakti\u00a0like Ambarish.\u00a0<br><\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignfull size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"903\" height=\"508\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-69.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4870\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-69.png 903w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-69-300x169.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-69-768x432.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 903px) 100vw, 903px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Then we have prema bhaktas\u00a0like Hanuman, who have attained a very high state of prema. And they&#8217;re always engaged in service to the Lord.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignfull size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"903\" height=\"508\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-70.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4871\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-70.png 903w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-70-300x169.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-70-768x432.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 903px) 100vw, 903px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Then we get devotees called prema-para&nbsp;devotees,&nbsp;who have a more intimate relationship to the Lord, like Arjuna with Krishna, or the Pandavas with Krishna.&nbsp;So, this is prema with some intimacy and basically it&#8217;s with Krishna.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignfull size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"903\" height=\"508\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-71.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4872\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-71.png 903w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-71-300x169.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-71-768x432.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 903px) 100vw, 903px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>And above this, we&#8217;ve got the prema-atura\u00a0bhaktas, who are very intimate with the Lord, and are constantly with the Lord, like Uddhava and the Yadavas.<br><\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignfull size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"903\" height=\"508\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-72.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4873\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-72.png 903w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-72-300x169.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-72-768x432.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 903px) 100vw, 903px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>So, we have various levels of devotees, so they don&#8217;t all get the same result.\u00a0According to their type of bhakti and prema, they get different results. At the same time, if they get to Vaikuntha, there&#8217;s no real hierarchy of higher and lower, they more or less, they\u00a0feel equal.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>What happens to the devotees of Krishna, who have very, very strong bhakti and they only want to be servants of Radha.\u00a0What happens to them?<br><\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignfull size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"903\" height=\"508\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-73.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4874\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-73.png 903w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-73-300x169.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-73-768x432.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 903px) 100vw, 903px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Do the people of Vrindavan,\u00a0do they get the same result as everybody else or do they get something special?\u00a0Do Nanda and Yasoda get the same destination as everybody else? So then, of course, Uttara says they shouldn\u2019t, they should get something much superior but then she&#8217;s asking this to Parikshit, what is the destination of [Laughs] persons like Nanda and Yasoda and Gopis etc, they stay here in the material world or they get a higher place than Vaikuntha or what happens?<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignfull size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"903\" height=\"508\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-74.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4875\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-74.png 903w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-74-300x169.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-74-768x432.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 903px) 100vw, 903px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>So, to\u00a0answer this question, Parikshit begins to tell a story. So,\u00a0this is another story within a story\u00a0[Laughs]. So, it&#8217;s one of the\u00a0brahmana\u00a0when he meets Gopakumar and then\u00a0Gopakumar begins to tell his story to this brahmana [Laughs] about what happened to him.\u00a0So anyway, there was in Assam, Pragjyotisha, that&#8217;s in Assam, and Assam is kind of far northeast India, quite far from Bengal\u00a0and there was a poor brahmana. So, he was a brahmana, but he was ignorant of the scriptures.\u00a0And he wanted to get a lot of money\u00a0[Laughs].<br><\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignfull size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"903\" height=\"508\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-75.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4876\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-75.png 903w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-75-300x169.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-75-768x432.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 903px) 100vw, 903px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>So he worshipped Kamakhya, that is a form of Durga in that place in Assam. So,\u00a0she became very satisfied with his worship and she appeared to him in a dream.\u00a0\u00a0And she gave him a ten syllable\u00a0Gopala,\u00a0Madana Gopala mantra\u00a0[Laughs]. So,\u00a0the actual mantra is never described there\u00a0[Laughs], the ten syllable mantra it says. But in the commentary of Sanatana Goswami\u00a0there he quotes a little verse which explains the syllables of the mantra, but it is not normal language.\u00a0It doesn&#8217;t say, it starts with go and then there&#8217;s p like that. They use rather strange words to describe each syllable, like a code. It&#8217;s like a secret code\u00a0[Laughs].\u00a0And if you don&#8217;t know the code, you couldn&#8217;t figure out what the mantra was. So in other words, scriptures record mantras, but they also put them in some coded language. So unless you don&#8217;t know that language, you don&#8217;t know what the mantra is.\u00a0You can&#8217;t figure out what it is\u00a0[Laughs].\u00a0But the actual mantra is Gopijana Vallabhaya Svaha. If we figure out what those syllables mean in the description, it&#8217;s Gopijana Vallabhaya Svaha, ten syllable mantra.\u00a0<br><\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignfull size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"903\" height=\"508\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-76.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4877\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-76.png 903w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-76-300x169.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-76-768x432.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 903px) 100vw, 903px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>So, he began chanting that mantra according to the order of Durga Devi, but he didn&#8217;t know what the mantra was for. He didn&#8217;t know how to chant it properly. He didn&#8217;t know what the goal was, etc.\u00a0This is like Namabhasa [Laughs]. He got some effect, but not the final effect. So he got purified and he lost his desire for wealth.So he had the mantra, but he said, may\u00a0be there&#8217;s something better than this mantra.\u00a0What do we achieve with this mantra? May be something better is there. You know like this, so, he didn&#8217;t quite know what to think of this mantra, but he chanted it anyway.<br><\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignfull size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"903\" height=\"508\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-77.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4878\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-77.png 903w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-77-300x169.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-77-768x432.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 903px) 100vw, 903px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>So he became very detached, and he started wandering to different tirthas, holy places, and he would beg to maintain his body.&nbsp;When he was wandering in the bank of the Ganga, he saw a group of brahmanas. And most of them were householders.&nbsp;And they were very learned.&nbsp;And they were performing all of their duties as a brahmana. And then he heard them speak about doing your nitya, naimittika karmas, and your kamya karmas. And then they said, we do all of these activities, then we can go to Svargaloka.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignfull size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"903\" height=\"508\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-78.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4879\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-78.png 903w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-78-300x169.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-78-768x432.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 903px) 100vw, 903px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>So, he was a little attracted for some time, but then he continued to chant his mantra, because Durga Devi had given him this mantra, so he continued to chant privately when the brahmanas weren&#8217;t watching him\u00a0[Laughs]. So,\u00a0because of the power of the mantra, he was not attracted to those rituals, and he wasn&#8217;t attracted to Svargaloka.<br><\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignfull size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"903\" height=\"508\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-79.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4880\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-79.png 903w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-79-300x169.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-79-768x432.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 903px) 100vw, 903px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>So, he left that place, and he went to Kasi, that is Varanasi.\u00a0There, the brahmanas were speaking about liberation. And they said, it&#8217;s very easy to get liberation. So he listened, and he began to accept their opinion.\u00a0So,\u00a0he heard them glorify renunciation, giving up everything, and liberation.<br><\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignfull size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"903\" height=\"508\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-80.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4881\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-80.png 903w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-80-300x169.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-80-768x432.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 903px) 100vw, 903px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>This\u00a0was a famous bathing place there, Manikarnika, and he would bathe there everyday in the Ganga. And there&#8217;s also a very famous deity of Shiva there in Kasi, Vishweswara, Vishweswara Shiva.\u00a0A very famous deity is there, in Kasi. So he would go see the deity, and then he would eat some tasty food\u00a0[Laughs], and survive that way\u00a0[Laughs].<br><\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignfull size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"903\" height=\"508\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-81.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4882\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-81.png 903w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-81-300x169.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-81-768x432.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 903px) 100vw, 903px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>But he continued to chant his mantra, his\u00a0Madana Gopala mantra and he became very attracted to the deity that is Krishna deity and that mantra. Then he got the highest bliss from this. So then,\u00a0he was not so enthusiastic about liberation, or bathing\u00a0and sannyasa\u00a0etc,\u00a0and he just wanted to chant this mantra.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignfull size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"903\" height=\"508\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-82.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4883\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-82.png 903w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-82-300x169.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-82-768x432.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 903px) 100vw, 903px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>So, finally Shiva spoke to him.\u00a0He said, you\u00a0don&#8217;t take sannyasa, you go to Mathura [Laughs]. You go to the Vrindavan forest\u00a0and\u00a0there your desires will be fulfilled. So,\u00a0he started going to Mathura, so he was in Varanasi, and he was going towards Mathura, but he came to Prayag\u00a0or Allahabad\u00a0on the way\u00a0and then he met some Vaishnavas there.\u00a0<br><\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignfull size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"903\" height=\"508\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-83.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4884\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-83.png 903w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-83-300x169.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-83-768x432.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 903px) 100vw, 903px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>And those Vaishnavas\u00a0were worshipping the deity of Madhava, that&#8217;s the Bindu Madhava deity. And he was attracted to that worship. But at the same time, then he thought, I have a deity mantra, and this deity of my mantra is different from that deity\u00a0[Laughs].\u00a0It\u00a0was different\u00a0[Laughs]. It&#8217;s different. The deity there\u00a0is different from the deity of my mantra.\u00a0<br>So, he said, in my mantra I have this Krishna\u00a0and He&#8217;s got His cowherd friends and the cows in the forest, He\u00a0has a flute in His house, He is decorated\u00a0with\u00a0the forest ornaments, but this\u00a0deity here is much different\u00a0[Laughs].\u00a0<br><\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignfull size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"903\" height=\"508\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-84.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4885\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-84.png 903w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-84-300x169.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-84-768x432.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 903px) 100vw, 903px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Yeah, Krishna is different from that deity. So then, the Madhava deity gave him some instruction. So He\u00a0says, you remember the words of Shiva? He said, you go to Vrindavan, so you go there\u00a0[Laughs], go on the Yamuna\u00a0and go to Vrindavan.\u00a0So, he continued on his way, and he got to Keshi\u00a0tirtha. That&#8217;s where Keshi was killed. And there in the forest, he heard somebody crying out.\u00a0<br><\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignfull size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"903\" height=\"508\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-85.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4886\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-85.png 903w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-85-300x169.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-85-768x432.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 903px) 100vw, 903px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>So,\u00a0he searched around, and then in a Kadamba forest, he saw a young cowherd boy\u00a0[Laughs], who&#8217;s dressed like a cowherd. So this is Gopakumar. He met Gopakumar.\u00a0So, this is the Gopakumar.\u00a0After Gopakumar had all of his experiences\u00a0and had gone to the spiritual world, and gone everywhere\u00a0[Laughs], he&#8217;d come back, and he was sitting there, and he was crying in ecstasy. This is when the brahmana met him.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>So, this Gopakumar looked something like his,\u00a0deity of his mantra, because he realized this\u00a0Krishna and his [Laughs]\u00a0is very similar, so he was pretty happy.\u00a0<br><\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignfull size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"903\" height=\"508\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-86.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4887\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-86.png 903w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-86-300x169.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-86-768x432.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 903px) 100vw, 903px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>So then, Gopakumar was thinking how to educate this person\u00a0[Laughs]. So then,\u00a0he thought that actually he should directly see Krishna. But to do that, he should not just chant this mantra, but he should do Sankirtan, of Krishna&#8217;s name, Nama Sankirtan, and this is very powerful to get\u00a0darshan\u00a0of Krishna. And he should stay in the places where Krishna had His\u00a0pastimes.<br><\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignfull size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"903\" height=\"508\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-87.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4888\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-87.png 903w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-87-300x169.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-87-768x432.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 903px) 100vw, 903px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>So then Gopakumar begins to tell his own story of how he realized Krishna, and he tells this story to the brahmana.\u00a0So, Gopakumar was a\u00a0cowherd in Vrindavan on earth. And one day he saw this saintly person there. So, this person told him to bathe in the Keshi ghat\u00a0and then get the mercy of Krishna.\u00a0So that Guru\u00a0then gave him the same mantra that the brahmana was chanting, the Madana Gopala mantra. Later on, the Lord explains, actually I became the Guru\u00a0[Laughs]. The Lord himself became the guru and gave the mantra\u00a0[Laughs].<br><\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignfull size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"903\" height=\"508\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-90.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4891\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-90.png 903w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-90-300x169.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-90-768x432.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 903px) 100vw, 903px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Okay, so when you get the mantra, the mantra of course is secret, it&#8217;s given secretly by the Guru to the disciple.\u00a0And generally, traditionally, when they get these mantras, then they have to learn the method of chanting. So there&#8217;s a bija of the mantra, there&#8217;s a deity, [Not clear]\u00a0deity of the mantra\u00a0etc, you have to do nyasas with the mantra, place the syllables of the mantra on your body, and there&#8217;s karanyasa and anganyasa\u00a0and things like this you have to do,\u00a0before you start chanting the mantra. There&#8217;s many things you have to do,\u00a0to purify yourself before you begin chanting.\u00a0So anyway, he began to explain, but he was starting to explain who is the, you know, what this mantra means, you know about Krishna. And then when he started describing Krishna, he fainted\u00a0[Laughs]. He cried and fainted and whatever\u00a0[Laughs]. And then he disappeared.\u00a0<br><\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignfull size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"903\" height=\"508\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-91.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4892\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-91.png 903w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-91-300x169.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-91-768x432.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 903px) 100vw, 903px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Okay, so then at least he understood, okay this is a mantra about the Supreme Lord\u00a0etc, and began chanting.\u00a0[Discussion aside].\u00a0So anyway, he began chanting the mantra and he understood its about the Supreme Lord.<br><\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignfull size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"903\" height=\"508\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-97.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4898\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-97.png 903w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-97-300x169.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-97-768x432.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 903px) 100vw, 903px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>So he also became completely disinterested in all relatives etc, etc [Laughs].\u00a0And he just wandered on the bank of the Ganga\u00a0chanting this mantra.<br><\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignfull size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"903\" height=\"508\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-92.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4893\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-92.png 903w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-92-300x169.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-92-768x432.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 903px) 100vw, 903px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>And as he was wandering on the bank of the Ganga, then he saw a poor brahmana who was worshipping a Salagrama,\u00a0but he was worshipping very simply because he was very poor. So, he began praising the brahmana for his worship.\u00a0But it was very simple worship.\u00a0So the brahmana said, actually if you want to see real worship, you go to this city where there&#8217;s a king and he does very, very nice worship of Vishnu. So, you can see the Lord of the Universe there.\u00a0The king is worshipping the Lord of the Universe. You go there and you&#8217;ll be very, very satisfied.<br><\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignfull size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"903\" height=\"508\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-88.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4889\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-88.png 903w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-88-300x169.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-88-768x432.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 903px) 100vw, 903px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>So Gopakumar\u00a0went to that city, he saw everything, he saw the deity, he saw the nice worship and he was very happy.\u00a0The king of the country had no son\u00a0[Laughs]. So, the king became very attracted to this Gopakumar\u00a0and his very good qualities, he treated him like a son\u00a0[Laughs] and he adopted him as his son.\u00a0And then the king died.<br><\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignfull size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"903\" height=\"508\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-89.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4890\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-89.png 903w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-89-300x169.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-89-768x432.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 903px) 100vw, 903px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignfull size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"907\" height=\"511\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-93.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4894\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-93.png 907w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-93-300x169.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-93-768x433.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 907px) 100vw, 907px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>So,\u00a0Gopakumar became the king\u00a0[Laughs]\u00a0of the kingdom\u00a0[Laughs]. So,\u00a0he, of course, did his duty and he was worshipping the Lord, he improved the worship of Vishnu even more.\u00a0And then he would feed all\u00a0of\u00a0the saintly people with the prasad from the deity.<br><\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignfull size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"903\" height=\"508\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-99.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4900\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-99.png 903w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-99-300x169.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-99-768x432.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 903px) 100vw, 903px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>But, even though he was the king, he continued to chant his mantra very quietly and he would take only the prasadam of the deity.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignfull size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"903\" height=\"508\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-94.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4895\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-94.png 903w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-94-300x169.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-94-768x432.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 903px) 100vw, 903px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>So, due to chanting that mantra, he became very dissatisfied in being the king, he wasn&#8217;t very interested in affairs so he gave all the management of the kingdom to the relatives of the king. But because he had been the king, people respected him\u00a0a lot and this created an obstacle, he couldn&#8217;t chant properly because of lot of interruptions from people\u00a0[Laughs].\u00a0And they had one custom and that is, the Lord&#8217;s prasadam, if it got touched by some outsider, they considered it contaminated, so they wouldn&#8217;t touch it anymore, they would throw it out\u00a0[Laughs]. So,\u00a0he was not very satisfied with that\u00a0[Laughs].<br><\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignfull size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"903\" height=\"508\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-95.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4896\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-95.png 903w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-95-300x169.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-95-768x432.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 903px) 100vw, 903px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>So then, he met some devotees from Puri\u00a0and they began describing Jagannatha [Laughs].\u00a0So,\u00a0they described this form made out of wood and they described the prasadam, even if it&#8217;s touched by anybody, impure or whatever, there&#8217;s no problem with that, people still eat it\u00a0[Laughs].<br><\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignfull size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"903\" height=\"508\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-96.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4897\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-96.png 903w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-96-300x169.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-96-768x432.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 903px) 100vw, 903px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>So,\u00a0they glorified that place and said even the donkeys have four arms\u00a0there\u00a0[Laughs]. Anyone who goes there never takes birth again\u00a0[Laughs].<br><\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignfull size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"903\" height=\"508\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-98.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4899\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-98.png 903w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-98-300x169.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-98-768x432.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 903px) 100vw, 903px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>So then, this Gopakumar\u00a0became very, very eager to go there, so he went there. So when he got to the temple,\u00a0then\u00a0from a distance he saw the big face of Jagannatha with His\u00a0big eyes. He had a dark color like the rain clouds.\u00a0And He had bright red lips.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignfull size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"903\" height=\"508\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-100.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4901\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-100.png 903w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-100-300x169.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-100-768x432.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 903px) 100vw, 903px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>So, he was so excited, he began to run towards the deity and embrace it\u00a0[Laughs]. And he didn&#8217;t actually know what he was doing but then the guards, the priests stopped him.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignfull size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"903\" height=\"508\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-101.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4902\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-101.png 903w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-101-300x169.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-101-768x432.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 903px) 100vw, 903px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Anyway, he was very satisfied there in Puri and he thought, now I&#8217;ve got the final result of my chanting because I see the Supreme Lord. So, he even became less interested in chanting because he felt so happy there. But then he felt, I have to serve this deity, but he wasn&#8217;t allowed to serve the deity, so he felt dissatisfied.\u00a0<br><\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignfull size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"903\" height=\"508\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-102.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4903\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-102.png 903w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-102-300x169.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-102-768x432.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 903px) 100vw, 903px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>And one day then he saw his Guru. So the Guru\u00a0said, actually this mantra is service to Jagannatha. Chanting this mantra is service to Jagannatha.\u00a0Don&#8217;t leave the chanting. So he said, by the power of this mantra you will live a long time and you will get the form of a cowherd boy. And you&#8217;ve\u00a0developed the right mentality for tasting the final results of this mantra.\u00a0Mentality, proper mentality to get the result of the mantra.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignfull size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"903\" height=\"508\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-103.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4904\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-103.png 903w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-103-300x169.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-103-768x432.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 903px) 100vw, 903px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>So, after that the Guru\u00a0disappeared again\u00a0[Laughs]. So he began chanting very enthusiastically and he was very happy.\u00a0So,\u00a0he would see the Lord\u00a0and then he would chant his mantra and that was his service.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignfull size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"903\" height=\"508\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-104.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4905\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-104.png 903w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-104-300x169.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-104-768x432.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 903px) 100vw, 903px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Then the king of Puri died\u00a0[Laughs]. The king had a son, but the son also renounced everything and he refused to take the kingdom.\u00a0So,\u00a0the ministers, they went to Jagannatha\u00a0and said, what are we going to do\u00a0[Laughs]? So then Jagannatha\u00a0said, you go to Gopakumar, he can be the king\u00a0[Laughs]. So the ministers came to Gopakumar\u00a0and they made him the new king\u00a0[Laughs].<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignfull size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"903\" height=\"508\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-105.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4906\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-105.png 903w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-105-300x169.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-105-768x432.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 903px) 100vw, 903px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>So, again he felt dissatisfied because he wanted to serve Jagannatha\u00a0in a special way but he wasn&#8217;t allowed to\u00a0[Laughs].\u00a0He also became distracted because he had to rule the kingdom.<br><\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignfull size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"903\" height=\"508\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-106.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4907\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-106.png 903w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-106-300x169.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-106-768x432.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 903px) 100vw, 903px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>So, he celebrated all the festivals including the Ratha Yatra in a very grand way. But still he wasn&#8217;t feeling very happy.\u00a0So, then he said, I&#8217;m going to give up the kingdom. He gave it to the ministers and the relatives\u00a0[Laughs]\u00a0and he resigned\u00a0[Laughs]. But still the people were giving him great respect.\u00a0So he didn&#8217;t feel very happy there and he wanted to leave.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignfull size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"903\" height=\"508\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-107.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4908\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-107.png 903w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-107-300x169.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-107-768x432.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 903px) 100vw, 903px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>And then\u00a0Jagannatha spoke to him\u00a0[Laughs]. So then Jagannatha said, don&#8217;t lament.\u00a0So Gopakumar\u00a0was thinking, should I leave this place? But if I leave then I&#8217;m leaving Jagannatha. I don&#8217;t want to leave Jagannatha. So what should I do? So then Jagannatha\u00a0said, you should leave.\u00a0Go to Mathura. So,\u00a0if you go there then, you will see me in the form that you really desire.<br><\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignfull size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"903\" height=\"508\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-108.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4909\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-108.png 903w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-108-300x169.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/02\/image-108-768x432.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 903px) 100vw, 903px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Okay, so\u00a0that&#8217;s chapter 1. No, chapter 2 is next.\u00a0Anyway, we can stop there.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center has-large-font-size\"><strong>Q &amp; A:<\/strong><strong><\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>1.) Maharaj, <\/strong><strong>b<\/strong><strong>oth B<\/strong><strong>rahma<\/strong><strong>na <\/strong><strong>and <\/strong><strong>Gopakumar <\/strong><strong>when the<\/strong><strong>y st<\/strong><strong>ar<\/strong><strong>t chant<\/strong><strong>ing the <\/strong><strong>mantra<\/strong><strong>&nbsp;<\/strong><strong>t<\/strong><strong>hey<\/strong><strong>&nbsp;<\/strong><strong>are <\/strong><strong>in <\/strong><strong>i<\/strong><strong>gnoranc<\/strong><strong>e<\/strong><strong>,<\/strong><strong>&nbsp;witho<\/strong><strong>ut <\/strong><strong>know<\/strong><strong>ing the<\/strong><strong>&nbsp;<\/strong><strong>meanin<\/strong><strong>g of <\/strong><strong>mantra<\/strong><strong>.<\/strong><strong>&nbsp;<\/strong><strong>Th<\/strong><strong>en how<\/strong><strong>&nbsp;they<\/strong><strong>&nbsp;are <\/strong><strong>like<\/strong><strong>&nbsp;<\/strong><strong>progres<\/strong><strong>sing?<\/strong><strong><\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Well, just like we chant Harinama, then we get some effect. But you don&#8217;t get full effect if you don&#8217;t chant. So,&nbsp;even with this mantra, because the name of the Lord is in there, they got some effect. Other mantras generally, even other mantras of Vishnu etc, don&#8217;t have such effect. You have to know everything about it and chant properly the mantra. Name, of course, is different, but the mantra is different.&nbsp;Krishna mantras are special. So that even those mantras, if not chanted properly, they give some effect.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Devotee:<\/strong>&nbsp;How he was able to understand&nbsp;?&nbsp;He is recognizing this, he is distinguishing. How then, he was ignorant&nbsp;but still he recognized that this is not my name.&nbsp;[Not clear]<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>HH Bhanu Swami Maharaj:<\/strong>&nbsp;Well, the mantra, because it&#8217;s Krishna. So, he became more attracted to Krishna [Laughs].<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>2.) <\/strong><strong>&nbsp;More importance is given to renunciation<\/strong><strong>, to renounce everything<\/strong><strong>?<\/strong><strong><\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Well, because he was king&nbsp;[Laughs].&nbsp;And that was a distraction from chanting the mantra etc. So, it&nbsp;was interruption to his worship. So therefore,&nbsp;he gave up those services.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>3.) So, is this <\/strong><strong>a<\/strong><strong>lso<\/strong><strong>&nbsp;<\/strong><strong>a special pastime? This Gopakumar [Not clear].<\/strong><strong><\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Well,&nbsp;this is the story to illustrate certain things. Of course,&nbsp;we can say the story itself becomes real. It&#8217;s not, he didn&#8217;t borrow the story from some Purana or anything.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>4.) Gopakumar was first in Vrindavan and then he left?<\/strong><strong><\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Yes, he was a cowherd in Vrindavan.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Devotee:<\/strong>&nbsp;If he was in Vrindavan then how he left Vrindavan and went?<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>HH Bhanu Swami Maharaj:<\/strong>&nbsp;He chanted the mantra when he got initiation from the Guru,&nbsp;then he lost interest in family life and he wandered around and then he met the brahmanas or the brahmana doing the worship and then he went to the city and&nbsp;then he went to Puri and all this.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>5.) Maharaj, now in kali yuga, yuga dharma is Nama Sankirtan <\/strong><strong>.<\/strong>Nama,&nbsp;rupa,&nbsp;guna,&nbsp;lila&nbsp;<strong>[Not clear]<\/strong><strong><\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Nama,&nbsp;rupa,&nbsp;guna,&nbsp;lila. So, through the name we realize the form, then we realize the qualities then we realize the pastimes.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Devotee:<\/strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;How can we understand,&nbsp;can we think about nama very appropriate&nbsp;[Not clear]<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>HH Bhanu Swami Maharaj:<\/strong>&nbsp;Oh. By chanting one&nbsp;realizes&nbsp;the non&nbsp;difference of the&nbsp;name&nbsp;from Krishna, it&#8217;s non&nbsp;different. So in the name is the form, the qualities, and the pastimes that become realized in the&nbsp;chanting of the name itself. Okay. Hare Krishna.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Devotees:<\/strong>&nbsp;HH Bhanu Swami Maharaj ki jai!!! Srila Prabhupada ki jai!!!<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Brhad Bhagavatamrta -3| HH Bhanu swami Maharaj | ISKCON Japan | 6th Dec 2017 jaya r\u0101dh\u0101-m\u0101dhava ku\u00f1ja-vih\u0101r\u012bgop\u012bjana-va